headline: Is AST SpaceMobile’s (ASTS) Latest Funding Move a Turning Point for Its Long-Term Partnership Ambitions?
summary: AST SpaceMobile recently announced a follow-on equity offering of approximately US$23.9 million and provided an update on its third quarter results, reporting sales of US$14.74 million and reiterating its second-half 2025 revenue guidance of US$50.0 million to US$75.0 million. These developments come as the company advances toward launching its largest BlueBird 6 satellite in December and builds momentum through over US$1 billion in revenue commitments with major partners like Verizon,...
